    "### Key Findings and Financial Insights"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "2e98c7f5",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Based on the results from the correlation analysis, it is clear that repayment history variables are one of the best predictors for future defaulting. Variables such as MAX_PAY_STATUS, PAY_0, AVG_PAY_STATUS, PAY_2 to PAY_6 have positive correlation with default. Customers who have experience in delaying their payments have higher chances of defaulting in the future.\n",
    "\n",
    "However, variables pertaining to payment amounts and credit limits are negatively correlated to defaulting. The customers whose credit limit and payment amount are higher have low chances of defaulting. Variables relating to demographics are seen to have little impact compared to repayment behavior variables.\n",
    "\n",
    "These results show that one’s repayment history is one of the best indicators of future credit risk and can form an important variable in the models to be generated in this study."
   ]
